# SECTION 4: Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 End-to-End HTTP Request Flow in Flutter

This diagram shows the complete lifecycle of an HTTP request from a Flutter UI to a remote REST API and back.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[UI Widget - UserListScreen] -->|User opens screen| B[initState triggered]
    B --> C[Create Future via fetchUsers]
    C --> D[FutureBuilder subscribes to Future]
    D -->|ConnectionState waiting| E[Show CircularProgressIndicator]
    D -->|Await completes| F[http.get sends HTTP Request]
    F -->|Over network| G[Remote REST API Server]
    G -->|Processes request| H{Response Type}
    H -->|2xx Success| I[http.Response with body]
    H -->|4xx Client Error| J[Exception thrown]
    H -->|5xx Server Error| J
    H -->|SocketException| J
    I --> K[jsonDecode response body]
    K --> L[Map each JSON object to User model]
    L --> M[Return List User]
    M --> N[FutureBuilder rebuilds with data]
    N --> O[Render ListView of users]
    J --> P[snapshot.hasError true]
    P --> Q[Show error message widget]
```

## 4.2 Layered Architecture of a Networking Module

This block diagram maps the **separation of concerns** in a production-grade Flutter app's networking layer.

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph UI["UI Layer - Presentation"]
        U1[UserListScreen StatefulWidget]
        U2[UserDetailScreen StatefulWidget]
        U3[Widgets Text, ListView, Button]
    end

    subgraph STATE["State Management Layer"]
        S1[FutureBuilder]
        S2[StateNotifier Provider]
        S3[setState calls]
    end

    subgraph SERVICE["Service Layer - Business Logic"]
        V1[ApiService class]
        V2[AuthService class]
        V3[Repository pattern]
    end

    subgraph MODEL["Model Layer - Data Structures"]
        M1[User class with fromJson toJson]
        M2[Post class with fromJson toJson]
        M3[Custom Exception classes]
    end

    subgraph NETWORK["Network Layer - HTTP"]
        N1[http package]
        N2[dio package with interceptors]
        N3[dart convert jsonEncode jsonDecode]
    end

    U1 --> S1
    U2 --> S2
    S1 --> V1
    S2 --> V2
    V1 --> M1
    V2 --> M3
    V1 --> N1
    V2 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
```

## 4.3 JSON Parsing Workflow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Raw JSON String from API] -->|jsonDecode| B[Map String dynamic or List dynamic]
    B -->|fromJson factory| C[Typed Dart Model Object]
    C -->|toJson method| D[Map String dynamic]
    D -->|jsonEncode| E[JSON String for POST body]

    subgraph ManualApproach["Manual Approach"]
        F[Write fromJson by hand]
    end

    subgraph CodeGenApproach["Code Generation Approach"]
        G[Annotate model with jsonSerializable]
        H[Run build_runner build]
        I[Generated fromJson and toJson]
    end

    F --> C
    G --> H
    H --> I
    I --> C
```

## 4.4 REST API Resource Pattern

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Client App] -->|GET /api/users| B[List all users]
    A -->|GET /api/users/42| C[Get user 42]
    A -->|POST /api/users| D[Create new user]
    A -->|PUT /api/users/42| E[Update user 42 fully]
    A -->|PATCH /api/users/42| F[Update user 42 partially]
    A -->|DELETE /api/users/42| G[Delete user 42]

    subgraph Server["REST API Server"]
        H[Users Controller]
        I[Users Service]
        J[Users Database Table]
        H --> I
        I --> J
    end

    B --> H
    C --> H
    D --> H
    E --> H
    F --> H
    G --> H
```

> [!NOTE]
> **RESTful Convention:** A resource (e.g., `users`) is exposed as a URL path. The HTTP method indicates the action. Status codes indicate the outcome. The server is **stateless** — every request contains all info needed to process it.

## 4.5 Error Handling State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    Idle --> Pending: api call initiated
    Pending --> Success: response 2xx received
    Pending --> ClientError: response 4xx received
    Pending --> ServerError: response 5xx received
    Pending --> NetworkError: SocketException TimeoutException
    Success --> Idle: data delivered to UI
    ClientError --> Idle: error message shown
    ServerError --> Retry: user taps retry button
    NetworkError --> Retry: user taps retry button
    Retry --> Pending: re attempt call
    ClientError --> Auth: status 401 detected
    Auth --> RefreshToken: call token refresh API
    RefreshToken --> Idle: new token stored
    RefreshToken --> Logout: refresh failed
    Logout --> [*]
```

