## 2.4 The CRUD Paradigm Across All Three

Every persistence technique maps to the **CRUD** operations:

$$\text{CRUD} = \{ \text{Create}, \text{Read}, \text{Update}, \text{Delete} \}$$

For KTU exam purposes, you must know how to **map** these four operations to each storage technique:

| Operation | SharedPreferences | SQLite | Hive |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Create** | `setString(key, val)` | `INSERT INTO ...` | `box.put(key, val)` |
| **Read** | `getString(key)` | `SELECT ... FROM ...` | `box.get(key)` |
| **Update** | `setString(key, newVal)` | `UPDATE ... SET ...` | `box.put(key, newVal)` |
| **Delete** | `remove(key)` | `DELETE FROM ...` | `box.delete(key)` |

> [!NOTE]
> **Key Insight:** In Hive, **Update = Create** because putting a value at an existing key *overwrites* it. This is a common viva question.
