## ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Reasons for Mark Deduction in Data Persistence Questions:**
>
> 1. **Confusing SharedPreferences with a Database (–2 marks):** SharedPreferences is a key-value store, *not* a database. Writing "SharedPreferences uses SQL" is an instant 0 for that sub-question.
>
> 2. **Forgetting `WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()` in `main()` (–1 to –2 marks):** Without this, async calls before `runApp()` will throw a runtime error. This is a *very common* mistake.
>
> 3. **Using `commit()` on the UI thread (–1 mark):** Causes UI freezes. Always explain *why* `apply()` is preferred in production.
>
> 4. **String concatenation in SQL queries (–2 marks):** This is a SQL injection vulnerability. Always use `whereArgs` for parameterized queries.
>
> 5. **Not providing defaults with `??` operator when reading from SharedPreferences (–1 mark):** Missing keys return `null`, which crashes the app if not handled.
>
> 6. **Forgetting `await` in Hive box operations (–1 mark):** Hive operations are async; missing `await` leads to race conditions and stale data displays.
>
> 7. **Writing Hive code without mentioning `typeId` (–1 mark):** `typeId` is mandatory for `@HiveType` and is a favorite viva question.
>
> 8. **Not closing Hive boxes on app termination (–1 mark):** Data may not flush properly. Best practice is to call `box.close()` in `dispose()`.

