## 🧠 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rapid Revision Checklist — Memorize Before Exam:**

- [ ] **Data Persistence** = storing data across app restarts; three pillars: **SharedPreferences**, **SQLite**, **Hive**.
- [ ] **SharedPreferences** = XML-backed, key-value, small primitive data only, use `apply()` over `commit()`.
- [ ] **SQLite** = relational, SQL-based, ACID-compliant, supports complex queries and large data.
- [ ] **Hive** = pure Dart, NoSQL, no native code, cross-platform, O(1) lookups via hash maps.
- [ ] **typeId** in Hive `@HiveType` must be unique across the entire app.
- [ ] **HiveObject** base class gives free `.save()` and `.delete()` methods.
- [ ] **WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()** is mandatory before async ops in `main()`.
- [ ] **Parameterize SQL queries** with `whereArgs` to prevent SQL injection.
- [ ] **Transactions** in SQLite guarantee ACID properties — all-or-nothing execution.
- [ ] **Hive CE** is the current maintained version; the original `hive` package was archived in 2023.
- [ ] **CRUD mapping:** SharedPreferences = set/get/remove; SQLite = INSERT/SELECT/UPDATE/DELETE; Hive = put/get/delete.
- [ ] **Encryption:** Hive has built-in AES-256; SQLite needs SQLCipher; SharedPreferences needs EncryptedSharedPreferences.
- [ ] **Decision Rule:** Settings → SharedPreferences; Relational search → SQLite; Object cache → Hive.
- [ ] **Performance order (read):** Hive (O(1)) > SQLite (O(log n)) > SharedPreferences (O(1) by key, O(n) full scan).
- [ ] **Schema:** SQLite = required (DDL); Hive = not required; SharedPreferences = not applicable.
